<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1437,477,903]" box="[198,956,717,743]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,359,717,743]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Distribution.</emphasis>
Only known from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[690,753,717,743]" name="Chile" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Chile</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gallardo, V. A." box="[769,943,717,743]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="9 - 12" refId="ref34177" refString="Gallardo, V. A. (1969) Description of Salmacina chilensis n. sp. (Polychaeta, Serpulidae) from northern Chile. Boletin de la Sociedad de Biologia de Concepcion, 41, 9 - 12." type="journal article" year="1969">Gallardo 1969</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1437,477,903]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,456,757,783]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Nogueira, J. M. M. &amp; ten Hove, H. A." box="[628,991,757,783]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="151 - 161" refId="ref36459" refString="Nogueira, J. M. M. &amp; ten Hove, H. A. (2000) On a new species of Salmacina Claparede, 1870 (Polychaeta: Serpulidae), from Sao Paulo state, Brazil. Beaufortia, 50, 151 - 161." type="journal article" year="2000">Nogueira and ten Hove (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gallardo" authorityYear="1969" box="[1005,1239,757,782]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Salmacina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="chilensis">
<emphasis box="[1005,1239,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Salmacina chilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very different to any other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Claparede" authorityYear="1870" box="[432,556,797,822]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Salmacina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[432,556,797,822]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Salmacina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in terms of the large number of radioles present. Moreover, the arrangement of the teeth in the fin-and-blade collar chaetae (
<figureCitation box="[796,941,837,863]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="43.[151,255,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[268,1321,198,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-135@43.[265,1325,194,1770]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 10. A–D: Pyrgopolon ctenactis, from Baja California Sur, UMAR-Poly 107. A–B, operculum, lateral and aboral views. C: Pyrgopolon ctenactis, from Oaxaca, UMAR-Poly 93. C, operculum, lateral view. D: Pyrgopolon ctenactis, from Guerrero, UMAR-Poly 108. D, operculum, lateral view. E: Rhodopsis pusilla, from Bermuda, USNM 118145, neotype. E, operculum, lateral view. F–G: Salmacina chilensis, from Chile. F–G, collar chaetae, lateral view and detail. H–J: Salmacina tribranchiata, from Sinaloa. H, anterior part, dorsal view. I, collar chaeta. J, “Apomatus” chaeta. K: Semivermilia pomatostegoides, from Tripoli (Mediterranean). K, operculum, lateral view. (Fig. E, redrawn from Ben-Eliahu &amp; ten Hove, 1989. Figs F–G, redrawn from Gallardo, 1969. Fig. K, redrawn from Zibrowius, 1969)." pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Figs 10F–G</figureCitation>
) “is rather more reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ehlers" authorityYear="1887" box="[1331,1401,837,862]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Protis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1331,1401,837,862]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Protis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName box="[151,304,877,902]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Chitinopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,304,877,902]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Chitinopoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, than of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Nogueira &amp; ten Hove 2000: 157)" authorityName="Claparede" authorityYear="1870" baseAuthorityName="Nogueira &amp; ten Hove" baseAuthorityPageNumber="157" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[408,532,877,902]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Salmacina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[408,532,877,902]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Salmacina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (
<bibRefCitation author="Nogueira, J. M. M. &amp; ten Hove, H. A." box="[560,944,877,903]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="151 - 161" refId="ref36459" refString="Nogueira, J. M. M. &amp; ten Hove, H. A. (2000) On a new species of Salmacina Claparede, 1870 (Polychaeta: Serpulidae), from Sao Paulo state, Brazil. Beaufortia, 50, 151 - 161." type="journal article" year="2000">Nogueira &amp; ten Hove 2000: 157</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
